survey_response.review_text: **** *** **** *** *** *** **** We moved to different part of banglore and had to search for a new Dr for my 2 pregnancy.After listening to lot of positive reviews from our friend circle we consulted Dr Anita .I had spotting issues. For my first time i was on complete bed rest and had to take weekly injectionsr.I ws expecting a similar treatment which was suggested by other Drs but to my surprise Dr was completely confident about following regular activities. Explained to me all the details with patience . Best thing is she never scares you . You will be feeling safe with her at each stage of pregnancy. Shes well aware with all the latest updates. par with all the health advices received from foreign professionals.  I strongly recommend Dr Anita. Each pregnant lady deserves a Dr like her.

review.practice_name: Cloudnine Hospital

survey_response.review_text:
Normally I don't write feedback on social sites. But here I really want to write about Anitha Ma'am as it might help others.
 We shifted to Bangalore from Delhi six months back and approached almost 5-6 doctors. All were good but we were still skeptical and were not feeling confident. But after meeting Anitha Ma'am for the first time we were sure that we will be in safe hands. She is 10/10 in her work, understanding of new tech and making this journey comfortable. 

My topmost worry has always been that many doctors recommend those treatments which are not required and might harm you in long run. We all know that it's not about money for a patient but the side effects and emotional trauma involved. Also we can't do much about it as we are completely dependent on doctors' advice. But here it was a pleasant surprise to see the other side :)

She will try her best for the normal and painless delivery without any doubt. 

In short, if you are looking for a experienced, cool and genuine doctor then she is the best we have met so far. And in case you also opt her for this most important part of life then one day you will also write such a long feedback like me :)
All the best!

review.practice_name: Ninth Month - Woman and Child Healthcare Center

survey_response.review_text: Dr. Anitha Roa, is one of the few **** doctors available in Bangalore. I had a good experience with this Doctor. Throughout the consultation she has been very good though she doesn’t talk much but whatever queries we raise she responds to it immediately. She is always available 24/7 and responds to our call or SMS or Whatsapp. I had a normal delivery and my experience throughout the labor was just Awesome. I still cherish those moments when ever I think about it.  She used to advise me on weight management, diet and exercise like Yoga during my pregnancy. I always followed her advise and I am proud mother of my Son who turns 6 months in another 7 days. It has proved me right that, a healthy mother can always deliver a healthy baby through normal delivery and I am fortunate enough to be one among them. I will always recommend this Doctor to my friends, relatives or any well wisher or anyone who is reading my feedback now. I always wanted to put forth my feedback in this site coz I too went through all the feedbacks of other patients. Since me and my husband found more positive feedbacks from other mothers, we decided to go with this doctor and fortunately we landed in the safe hands. I always rate Dr. Anitha Rao 10 on 10. My best wishes for all the Expected Mothers.

review.practice_name: Ninth Month - Woman and Child Healthcare Center

survey_response.review_text: It was a wonderful experience. First time we had visited this doctor for our cousin. We found very nice. The way doctor speaks and gives the explanation was very nice. We started with this doctor when my wife conceived. My wife got very good confidence on the doctor consultation. We decided to continue with this doctor only. Staff in this clinic are also nice and cooperative. Appointment may not start exactly on the provided time because previous patients would be spending time with doctor to clear their doubts. So even though appointment may not start on time, We were happy because she provided all the details and clarifies our doubts. We were first time parents, so had many silly doubts which doctor clarified. We should not think much about appointment starting on time or little late. Focus was on mother and baby, which doctor provided. Doctor Anitha Rao had given all good and right directions thought out the pregnancy. She also advised on the type of diet my wife should have. Had not given any unnecessary medicines until it is needed. Doctor constantly monitored the weight and health of pregnant mother. Doctor had cleared all our doubts. Doctor had told that we always give preference to Normal delivery and continuously provided the right guidance like diet, exercise. Doctor had clearly told that walk atleast 30 minutes every day is must. So we blindly followed her advise. My wife delivered to baby girl. Both mother and Baby are healthy. I would recommend to this doctor.

survey_response.review_text:
Dr Anitha comes across as a very soft spoken,calm lady. Me & my wife deiced to meet only post reading a lot of positive reviews about her. 

I must say my wife felt very comfortable after consulting her. 
Dr Anitha has her clinic in Sahakarnagara and currently charges a nominal fee of 400 for consultation. She did not recommend any unnecessary tests, medication & even the checkup was only as per schedule. We felt she is approachable and clears any doubt during her consultation & also she does text back to your questions without losing her patience in case if your not able to meet her at the clinic.

We consulted her from the first time of confirmation of the pregnancy and today we are happy to have a one week old baby.

I have recommended Dr Anitha to my friends circle and all those of you who are looking for safe hands.
